Legs (
Figs 6a–c
). Claw normal in shape, without teeth. Unguis almost 8 times longer in inner length than unguiculus. Tita with blunt tenent hairs, 2 on dorsal and 1 on ventral side of front leg; 3 on dorsal and 1 on ventral side of middle leg; and 3 on dorsal side of hind leg, tenent hair on ventral side of hind leg absent (
Figs 6a–c
).

Ventral tube (
Fig. 7
). Ventral tube with 3 + 3 laterodistal and 2 + 2 posterior chaetae.

Body chaetotaxy (
Figs 8a–c
). Chaetae on dorso-medial line of Th. II – Abd. V: 6–7, 4/3–4, 3–5, 4–5, 5–6, 3–5 on each side (
Fig. 8b
). Macrochaetae on dorsal side of Th. II – Abd. V: 1, 1/0, 0, 0, 2, 4 on each side (
Fig. 8b
). Sensilla formula of Th. II – Abd. V: 2, 2/1, 1, 1, 1, 4 on each side (
Fig. 8a
). Microsensilla formula of Th. II – Abd. V: 0, 0/1, 0, 0, 0, 0 on each side (
Fig. 8a
). Ventro-medial chaetae of Th. I – Th. III as 0, 0, 3–6 on each side (
Fig. 8c
). Tenacular area with 6–11 ordinary chaetae. Furcal subcoxa area with 19–24 ordinary chaetae.
